data.enText: to slope or to make sth slope in a particular direction or at a particular angle
The sun slanted through the window.

data.chText: 把滑雪板略微向左斜一点。
data.enText: Slant your skis a little more to the left.

data.chText: 有倾向性地陈述；有偏向地报道
data.enText: to present information based on a particular way of thinking, especially in an unfair way

data.chText: 报告中的调查结果偏袒制造商。
data.enText: The findings of the report had been slanted in favour of the manufacturers.
The sofa faced the fire at a slant .
Cut the flower stems on the slant .
a way of thinking about sth, especially one that shows support for a particular opinion or side in a disagreement

data.chText: 她对那出戏提出了一种新的见解。
data.enText: She put a new slant on the play.

ex.chText: 只有当这架望远镜以30度角倾斜时，你才能看到那颗星星。
ex.enText: Only when the telescope is inclined at an angle of thirty degrees can you see that star.

ex.chText: 墙好像倾斜了将近15度角。
ex.enText: The wall seems to incline almost fifteen degrees.

synonyms.bx: 指（使）某物以某种角度或向某一方向倾斜。

ex.chText: 他身体前倾，想听他们在谈论什么。
ex.enText: He leaned forward and tried to catch what they were talking about.

ex.chText: 她正倚着一棵树等她男朋友。
ex.enText: She was leaning against a tree, waiting for her boyfriend.

ex.chText: 别把自行车斜靠在门上。
ex.enText: Don't lean your bicycle against the door.

synonyms.bx: 指某人身体前倾或某物倾斜，也可指（使）人或物倚靠在另一人或物之上。

ex.enText: Rays of the sun slanted through the window.

ex.chText: 他把滑雪板略微向右斜了一点。
ex.enText: He slanted his skis a little more to the right.

synonyms.bx: 指某物歪斜或使某物产生一定的角度。

ex.chText: 浴室的地面向排水口倾斜。
ex.enText: The floor of the bathroom slopes down to the drain.
The road slopes sharply at this point.

synonyms.bx: 指地面或其他表面倾斜。

ex.enText: She tilted her head and smiled.

ex.chText: 你可以看见他的嘴角微微翘起。
ex.enText: You can see his mouth tilt upwards slightly at the corners.
The little boy tilted his chair back.

synonyms.bx: 尤指头、下巴等身体部位倾斜或使其倾斜。

tr: degree of deviation from a horizontal plane
example: the roof had a steep pitch

tr: a biased way of looking at or presenting something

example: He biased his presentation so as to please the share holders

tr: to incline or bend from a vertical position

example: A scar slanted across his face

value.def: Something that slants is sloping, rather than horizontal or vertical.

example.ex: The morning sun slanted through the glass roof...
example.tran: 清晨的阳光透过玻璃屋顶，斜照了进来。

example.ex: Battered pine floors slanted down to a Georgian window.
example.tran: 破旧的松木地板歪歪斜斜地铺到一个乔治王时代风格的窗户跟前。

value.def: If something is on a slant, it is in a slanting position.

example.ex: You're slightly above the garden because the house is on a slant.
example.tran: 由于房子是倾斜的，所以你的位置稍微高于花园。

value.def: If information or a system is slanted, it is made to show favour towards a particular group or opinion.

example.ex: The programme was deliberately slanted to make the home team look good.
example.tran: 这个节目故意偏向主场队，以使他们看上去表现还不错。

value.tran: 使有倾向性;使有偏向性

example.ex: The electoral system, which is heavily slanted towards the ruling party, needs to be changed.
example.tran: 需要改变过于向执政党一方倾斜的大选体系。
带有倾向性的新闻报道

value.def: A particular slant on a subject is a particular way of thinking about it, especially one that is unfair.

example.ex: The political slant at Focus can be described as centre-right...
example.tran: 《焦点》杂志的政治立场可以称为中间偏右。

example.ex: They give a slant to every single news item that's put on the air.
example.tran: 他们播放的每一则新闻都有所偏向。

value.tran: (尤指有失偏颇的)观点，看法;偏向;偏袒
